g.text: used to quickly identify and quantitively characterized small variations at DWs. PCA is also a
promising tool to isolate the contribution of ferroelastic DWs.
Apart from DWs, Raman micro-spectroscopy and PCA could be used as complementary tools
to map with a microscopic resolution the distribution of strain in materials, as required in
silicon [42], graphene [43] or multilayer ceramic capacitors [44]. The use of PCA could also be
extended to 3D matrix obtained through other experimental techniques, such as surface
potential maps [45].
